==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Compression projectile
<hw>Com*pres"sion pro*jec"tile</hw>. <def>A projectile constructed so as
to take the grooves of a rifle by means of a soft copper band firmly
attached near its base or, formerly, by means of an envelope of soft
metal. In small arms the modern projectile, having a soft core and
harder jacket, is subjected to compression throughout the entire
cylindrical part.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Compressive</ent>⟦br⟧
